{"word":"H3700 - כָּסַף - kâçaph - kaw-saf' - Desire","slug":"H3700","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כָּסַף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kâçaph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kaw-saf'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Desire"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05E1;&#x05E3; - ka&#x0302;saph</b> - <i>kaw-saf'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to become <i>pale</i>, that is, (by implication) to <i>pine</i> after; also to <i>fear: - </i>[have] desire, be greedy, long, sore."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3701\">H3701</a>, <a href=\"#/H3703\">H3703</a>"}]}